  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "Certainly! When someone is looking to buy an air conditioner, there are several factors to consider to ensure they get the best unit for their needs. Here are some probing questions you might ask:\n\n1. **Room Size & Type:**\n   - How big is the room or space you want to cool? (Square footage or dimensions)\n   - Is the room open or does it have doors and walls separating it from other areas?\n\n2. **Existing Conditions:**\n   - Does the room receive a lot of sunlight or is it shaded most of the day?\n   - Are there a lot of electronic devices or appliances that generate heat in the room?\n\n3. **Usage Patterns:**\n   - How often will the air conditioner be used (e.g., daily, occasionally, seasonally)?\n   - Are you looking to cool the room quickly or maintain a consistent temperature throughout the day?\n\n4. **Installation Type:**\n   - Are you interested in a window unit, portable AC, wall-mounted unit, or central air conditioning system?\n   - Do you have a preference for professional installation or do you require a DIY-friendly unit?\n\n5. **Energy Efficiency:**\n   - How important is energy efficiency to you? Are you looking for a unit with a high SEER (Seasonal Energy Efficiency Ratio) rating?\n   - Are you concerned about long-term electricity costs?\n\n6. **Additional Features:**\n   - Do you need an air conditioner with advanced features like Wi-Fi capability, smart home integration, or programmable timers?\n   - Is having a quiet operation important to you, especially if the unit will be installed in a bedroom or home office?\n\n7. **Budget:**\n   - What is your budget for the new air conditioner?\n   - Are you open to financing options if the unit exceeds your immediate budget?\n\n8. **Maintenance & Durability:**\n   - Are you looking for a low-maintenance option?\n   - Is durability and a long-lasting product important for you?\n\n9. **Specific Brands or Models:**\n   - Do you have any preferred brands or models based on past experience or recommendations?\n\n10. **Air Quality:**\n   - Are you interested in additional air quality features like air purification or dehumidifying capabilities?\n\nGathering answers to these questions can help narrow down the options and find the most suitable air conditioner based on the user's specific needs and preferences.",
